          <p class="text-gray-700">AurumHandmade, emerging designer (6 months in business), sold through craft shows and Etsy. Built Squarespace site (November 2024): Portfolio template showcasing macro photography (hallmarks, stone settings visible), creation process blog (bench diary posts weekly), custom order form prominent (bespoke requests welcomed), styling tips blog (SEO content drives traffic). Results: Monthly sales grew from $3,200 (craft shows + Etsy) to $12,400 (Squarespace direct sales). 387% increase. Custom orders: 8/month at $800-1,500 average ($8,400/month bespoke revenue, was $0 before). Blog traffic: 4,200 monthly visitors (styling tips SEO), 12% convert to email list. Instagram followers: 2,100 → 8,400 (site content shared socially). Build cost: $1,200 (Squarespace annual $276 + custom domain $24 + product photography $600 + 15 hours designer time @ $20/hr). ROI: 387% sales increase, 2.5-month payback 12x. Key insight: Squarespace templates = portfolio-quality visuals without custom design cost. Macro photography + creation blog = storytelling that justifies premium pricing. Custom order form = bespoke revenue stream Etsy couldn't capture (Etsy buyers want production, Squarespace buyers want handmade unique). Blog SEO = organic traffic reduces Instagram dependency (4,200 monthly visitors, 12% email capture = 504 leads monthly). Squarespace wins for emerging jewelry designers under $15K/month who need portfolio elegance + basic e-commerce without Shopify complexity. But e-commerce features limited (no inventory tracking, manual order management required). Scale to Shopify when exceeding 50 orders/month.</p>
