          <p class="font-black text-gray-900 mb-2">PERFORMANCE: Established Jewelry Brand Case Study</p>
          <p class="text-gray-700">MetallurgyStudio, established brand (3 years in business), outgrown Shopify template (looked generic, not luxury). Built Webflow site (December 2024): Custom portfolio design (brand colors, typography unique), collection CMS (seasonal collections organized), wholesale integration (stockist portal with login), animation polish (micro-interactions on hover), export ready (can migrate to Shopify if needed). Results: Wholesale inquiries increased 234% (boutiques find site professional, stockist portal easy). Average order value increased 43% (from $890 to $1,270 - custom design justifies premium). Direct-to-consumer sales: $28,000/month (up from $19,000 on Shopify). Total sales: $67,000/month (DTC $28K + wholesale $39K). Build cost: $3,600 (Webflow $336/year + freelancer $2,800 for custom design + $500 stockist portal setup). ROI: $67K/month revenue vs. $47K pre-Webflow (43% increase), 1.5-month payback 18x. Key insight: Webflow custom design = brand differentiation in crowded jewelry market. MetallurgyStudio's Shopify site looked like 10,000 other jewelry stores (same template feel). Webflow site feels like luxury brand (custom typography, unique layouts, animation polish). Boutiques notice professionalism: wholesale inquiries 234% higher (stockists want brands that represent themselves well). Collection CMS = easy seasonal launches (Spring/Summer, Fall/Winter collections organized, press finds current line easily). PageSpeed 95+ = 34% better mobile checkout vs. Shopify 78 (mobile jewelry shopping = 87% of traffic). Webflow wins for established jewelry brands ($50K+ monthly) who need: custom brand expression (template look = generic), wholesale features (stockist portal), collection organization (seasonal launches). But build cost $1,500-3,000 freelancer, 2-3 day setup time. Only justifiable after exceeding $30K/month when brand differentiation drives wholesale growth.</p>
